How Can I Contribute?
1. Reporting Bugs
If you find a calculation error or a script crash:Check the Issues tab to see if it has already been reported.
If not, open a new issue.
Describe the input values ($p, r, t$) you used and the incorrect output you received.

2. Suggesting Enhancements
Want to add features (like Compound Interest or a Web UI)?

Open an issue labeled "enhancement."

Describe the feature and why it would be useful.



3. Pull Requests (Code Changes)
Ready to write some code? Follow these steps:

Fork the repository.

Create a Feature Branch (git checkout -b feature/AmazingFeature).

Commit your changes (git commit -m 'Add some AmazingFeature').

Push to the branch (git push origin feature/AmazingFeature).

Open a Pull Request.

Style Guidelines
Scripting: Please keep the Bash script clean and add comments for any complex logic.

Documentation: If you change how the script works, please update the README.md.

Commits: Use clear, descriptive commit messages (e.g., "Fix: handle decimal interest rates").

Community & Conduct
By participating in this project, you agree to abide by our Code of Conduct. Please be respectful and collaborative in all interactions.

Happy Coding!
